# ğŸ“ˆ Scalability & Security Notes (Very Important)

Add **this section below README or in a separate file** (both are acceptable).

```md
## ğŸ“ˆ Scalability & Security Design

### Authentication & Security
- Passwords are securely hashed using bcrypt with salt
- Stateless JWT authentication enables horizontal scaling
- Role-based access control enforced via middleware
- Input validation and error handling implemented across APIs
- Environment variables used for sensitive configurations

### Scalability Considerations
- Modular project structure allows easy addition of new modules
- Stateless APIs allow deployment behind load balancers
- MongoDB supports horizontal scaling via sharding
- Redis can be integrated for caching frequently accessed data
- Microservices-ready architecture with API versioning

### Deployment Readiness
- Backend can be containerized using Docker
- Frontend can be served via Nginx or CDN
- CI/CD pipelines can be integrated for automated deployments
